        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 7:37AM CST by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 736 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northeast of Broken Bow, or 17 miles northwest of De Queen,
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wickes...                         Grannis...
Vandervoort...                    Hartley...
Little Missouri Falls Recreatio...Cossatot River State Park...
Bard Springs Recreation Area...   Caney Creek Wilderness...
Albert Pike Recreation Area...    Shady Lake Recreation Area...
Hatton...                         Roaring Branch Natural Area...
New Hope in Pike County...        Bogg Springs...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
